ğŸ“Œ Add to Section 6. Recommended Logical Model
	â€¢	Human Access
	â€¢	Users are provisioned in IdP (external identity provider).
	â€¢	Groups and attributes (like team, role) flow into AWS via SAML/OIDC.
	â€¢	No manual IAM user creation in AWS.
	â€¢	AWS IAM is used only for roles, permission sets, and policies.

â¸»

ğŸ“Œ Add to Section Implementation Roadmap
	â€¢	Step 1: Confirm IdP integration (e.g., Azure AD â†’ AWS SSO).
	â€¢	Step 2: Create/manage users only in IdP (not in IAM console).
	â€¢	Step 3: Map IdP groups to AWS permission sets (least privilege).
	â€¢	Step 4: Regularly sync IdP groups with AWS IAM Identity Center.
	â€¢	Step 5: Enforce MFA at IdP level (centralized control).
